value.title: Pence returns to Arizona for final push to flip liberal-leaning cities
value.excerpt: In an effort to pick up voters from more progressive counties that voted against the president in 2016, Vice President Mike Pence is returning to the key battleground state of Arizona on Friday.

value.title: NFL legend Brett Favre endorses Trump for president
value.excerpt: NFL great Brett Favre has endorsed President Donald Trump for reelection. He's one of the most prominent figures in sports to publicly pledge support for the President.

value.title: Trump rips absentee ballot extensions, says election 'should end on November 3rd'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday panned decisions made by some courts that are allowing mail-in or absentee ballots to be counted if they are received by election authorities after Nov. 3, calling the rulings "CRAZY and so bad for our Country."

value.title: Pence To Hold Rallies In Flagstaff, Tucson On Friday: Livestreams
value.excerpt: With four days to go until Election Day, Vice President Mike Pence returns to Arizona to rally support from voters.

value.title: Criscrossing Texas: In U.S. Senate race, Hegar joins Kamala Harris, Cornyn rolls with Ted Cruz
value.excerpt: U.S. Sen. John Cornyn and his challenger, former Air Force pilot MJ Hegar, are getting some big-name boosts in the final stretch of their Senate race

value.title: John James slams Michigan Senate opponent, says Dems 'freaking out' as Biden, Obama storm state
value.excerpt: Michigan Senate candidate John James reacts on 'Fox & Friends' to Joe Biden and former President Barack Obama campaigning in his state.

value.title: With time short, Vice President Mike Pence returns in effort to keep Arizona red
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence will campaign in Flagstaff and Tucson as the presidential race in battleground Arizona goes down to the wire.

value.title: Biden attacks Trump's Covid-19 response in South Korean op-ed and promises 'principled diplomacy' with North Korea
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden attacked President Donald Trump's handling of the Covid-19 pandemic in an op-ed for a Korean media outlet Friday and promised to engage in "principled diplomacy" in pursuing the denuclearization of North Korea.

value.title: Candace Owens on Lil Wayne's Trump support: Liberals laughed at idea of 'Black Exit' by Dems
value.excerpt: Black Americans leaving the Democratic Party shows they have done nothing for the Black community, according to author Candace Owens on Friday.

value.title: Column: White House of Horrors: A Halloween-themed poem about Donald Trump
value.excerpt: The latest TrumPoem, a rhyming account of the presidency of Donald J. Trump, loosely based on his words and acts.

value.title: Pence highlights economic recovery report at Nevada rally
value.excerpt: RENO, Nev. (AP) — Vice President Mike Pence urged early in-person voting and highlighted reports of a partial economic recovery during a rally Thursday in Reno, hoping to drum up enthusiasm in Nevada in the final days before the election.

value.title: Pelosi: 'Confident' Biden to be elected President
value.excerpt: Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi says she's confident the Democratic Presidential nominee Joe Biden will be elected president. She says while she doesn't want to be "overconfident," she wants to be ready to "go down a different path.

value.title: Lil Wayne reveals 'great meeting' with Trump, prompting Twitter users to respond
value.excerpt: Lil Wayne made a big splash on Twitter after he revealed that he met with Trump, sharing a friendly photo the two of them took together.

value.title: Sean Hannity: Biden depicting ‘scary’ image of America despite surging economy
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is making America out to be a country besieged by doom and gloom with five days left until the election, but “Hannity” host Sean Hannity argued Thursday the nation is actually on an upswing.

value.title: Trump meets with Army unit that conducted Al-Baghdadi raid, awards citation
value.excerpt: President Trump has awarded a citation to the Army special operations unit that conducted the 2019 raid resulting in the death of notorious Islamic State leader Abu Bakr Al-Baghdadi.

value.title: Midwest Dems urge party to focus on infrequent Black voters rather than White voters who backed Trump
value.excerpt: Some local leaders say Democrats may be focusing too much on White working class voters who backed Trump and not enough on voters who didn't turn out at all.

value.title: The Latest: Trump meets troops involved in al-Baghdadi raid
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump quietly met with U.S. Special Forces troops involved in last year’s raid to kill Islamic State leader Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi

value.title: Trump's disrespect of Sen. Martha McSally was painful to watch
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump treated Sen. Martha McSally like a second-class citizen during his Goodyear rally. That's the thanks she gets, for her loyalty.

value.title: Trump is touting the record-shattering GDP report as evidence of a full economic rebound. Here's why the recovery actually has much further to go.
value.excerpt: The US economy grew 7.4% in Q3, or 33.1% at an annualized rate. Many economists say growth is slowing down without another stimulus package.

value.title: Glenn Greenwald leaves The Intercept, claiming he was ‘censored’ over an article he wrote on Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Journalist Glenn Greenwald said Thursday that he was leaving The Intercept, the news website he helped found, claiming that it had refused to publish an article he wrote on Joe Biden unless he removed sections that were critical of the Democratic presidential nominee.

value.title: Retired Minnesota police officers asked to be Trump poll watchers in 'rough neighborhoods'
value.excerpt: A volunteer attorney for the Trump 2020 campaign is seeking retired officers to work as poll challengers in Minnesota.

value.title: Former Michigan Gov. Rick Snyder on being a 'proud Republican' who voted for Biden
value.excerpt: Snyder served eight years as governor and was replaced by Democrat Gretchen Whitmer in 2019.

value.title: Chuck Todd Slammed For Saying Joe Biden Takes COVID-19 'Too Seriously'
value.excerpt: The MSNBC host said that Biden was accepting a smaller footprint by not engaging in high-risk campaign acitivities

value.title: America is changing. Joe Biden can help us through the transformation.
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is more than just the stop-the-madness alternative to an unhinged incumbent. He has the potential to be a transformational president who guides the nation through an inevitable period of wrenching change.

value.title: Biden, Cunningham hold narrow leads in North Carolina: poll
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden has a narrow lead over President Trump in North Carolina, while Democrat Cal Cunningham holds a similarly slim lead in the Tarheel State’s marquee Senate race in a new survey released Thursday.
